name: Square Cafe
location_description:
Everyone, Check Facebook for updates.

Monteverde‚Äôs Produce has donated fresh produce to our grocery store. We will be setting up outside of the Caf√© TODAY for folks to come and take what they need FOR FREE- NO QUESTIONS ASKED. We will be monitoring safe distances so you can pick up your FREE produce quickly and safely. Please take advantage of this if you need food or have been put in a ficial pinch.

PLEASE NOTE: We are a small business as well so if you are not in need ficially but have grocery and food needs, please consider shopping our groceries located on our website for carryout or delivery.

SAFETY RULES:
- YOU MUST WEAR GLOVES! (We will provide them for you)
- ONE AT A TIME!
- THE NEXT PERSON IN LINE MUST STAND AT THE FIRST TAPE MARK! (6 FEET OF SAFE DISTANCE)
- EVERY PERSON IN LINE WILL NEED TO STAND AT A 6 FOOT TAPE MARK!
- DO NOT GO TO THE NEXT TAPE MARK OR SHOP THE TABLE UNTIL THE PREVIOUS PERSON HAS FULLY LEFT THE AREA!
GO HOME, WASH YOUR HANDS, WASH YOUR PRODUCE, AND ENJOY!, Will assess again on Monday, March 23 if giving away food again

name: Dormont Little Free Pantry
location_description:
All are welcome, Pantry box is located on the front porch of the house.  It can be accessed any time - no appointment is needed.  Please note that some foods may be brought inside at night (e.g., canned and jarred goods) if the temperature drops below freezing - this is to ensure food safety.  If you are in need of particular items (e.g., baby products) or have special food needs (e.g., allergies, celiac, etc.), you can email us at hatefreedormont@gmail.com and we will do our best to source items for you and schedule a pick-up time, We rely on donations, but have tried to encourage donors to give the following items:
-Bags of rice, bags/boxes of beans and rice mix (e.g., red beans and rice)
-Canned vegetables, fruits, and soups
-Cereals, oats, and shelf stable milk
-Mac and cheese, pasta, and jarred sauce
-Individually wrapped rolls of toilet paper
-Hygiene products including soaps, shampoos, toothpaste, tooth brushes, and menstrual pads
-Snacks (e.g., goldfish crackers, snack packs), The pantry box is available 24/7, no appointments are needed.  Please note that some foods may not be available if the temperature is too low or high for food safety reasons since this is an outdoor location, Front Porch

name: Lawrenceville United
location_description:
Lawrenceville residents preferred, From Butler Street, head north (towards the Allegheny River) onto 51st Street. Turn right as if accessing the parking lot for Thriftique / Allegheny Health Network. Follow driveway to rear of building. The food distribution location is in the rear of that building, by the loading docks, in the approximate middle of the building, We are practicing social distancing. Please maintain 6 feet distance from us and others at all times. We ask you remain in your vehicle and pop the trunk and we will load the box directly into the trunk. 

We receive the donations from Whole Foods through 412 Food Rescue. We can't anticipate what will come and how much, Friday afternoons. Please call Lawrenceville United at 412-802-7220 by 11 a.m. on Fridays to get on our list to receive a box of food. Leave your number and we will call you when it's ready, Rear

name: Carnegie Mellon University Pantry
location_description:
The Carnegie Mellon University Pantry is a need-blind resource that is open only to current CMU students. All current students, including both undergraduate and graduate students, are welcome to visit our Pantry and take food once per week, Call the phone number listed on the Pantry sign in the front door of the Residence on Fifth to gain access to the building, All orders from the CMU Pantry include a standardized package of staple foods, including fresh produce, protein, canned fruits/vegetables, quick meals, soups, pasta/rice, potatoes, cereal, snacks, and miscellaneous items if available. All orders also include a cleaning/hygiene item. Additionally, shoppers are able to choose from a limited number of other items in the Pantry to customize their orders. Shoppers can fill out the online order form by visiting the CMU Pantry website, Monday | 3:00 pm - 5:00 pm
